  "response": "Yes, absolutely. Money laundering is a serious crime in virtually every country. It's the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear to come from a legitimate source. The purpose is to integrate \"dirty\" money into the legitimate financial system.\n\nThink of it this way: someone commits a crime, like drug trafficking or fraud, and gets a lot of money. They can't just deposit that money into a bank account without raising suspicion. So, they try to \"clean\" it by disguising its origin through a series of transactions.\n\nThere are usually severe penalties for money laundering, including hefty fines, imprisonment, and asset forfeiture.\n",
